ution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Of uncertain origin; it was not in general use before the late 18th century. It may be a Latinate variant of the biblical name   Adah .  However, it has also been explained as a pet form of   Adele   and   Adelaide  , Germanic female names of which the first element is <i>adal</i> ‘noble’. It was borne by a 7th-century abbess of Saint-Julien-des-Prés at Le Mans."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"Ada de Dunbar was born in 1227, in Dunbar, Haddingtonshire, Scotland. She married William Hume II. They were the parents of at least 1 son."},"et":{"1227–":"1227–Surnud","1225–1299":"1225–1299","1260–1300":"1260–1300","1227–Female":"1227–Surnud","1227":"1227","1225":"1225","1300":"1300","1299":"1299","1260":"1260","Dunbar Castle, East Lothian, Scotland":"Dunbar, Haddingtonshire, Scotland","Hume, Berwickshire, Scotland":"Hume, Berwickshire, Šotimaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1227–":"1227–Kuollut","1225–1299":"1225–1299","1260–1300":"1260–1300","1227–Female":"1227–Kuollut","1227":"1227","1225":"1225","1300":"1300","1299":"1299","1260":"1260","Dunbar Castle, East Lothian, Scotland":"Dunbar, Haddingtonshire, Scotland","Hume, Berwickshire, Scotland":"Hume, Berwickshire, Skotlanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"1227–":"1227–Décédée","1225–1299":"1225–1299","1260–1300":"1260–1300","1227–Female":"1227–Décédée","1227":"1227","1225":"1225","1300":"1300","1299":"1299","1260":"1260","Dunbar Castle, East Lothian, Scotland":"Dunbar, Haddingtonshire, Écosse","Hume, Berwickshire, Scotland":"Hume, Berwickshire, Écosse, Royaume-Uni","lifeSummary":"Ada de Dunbar est née en 1227, à Dunbar, Haddingtonshire, Écosse. Elle a épousé William Hume II. Ils ont eu au moins 1 fils."},"de":{"1227–":"1227–Verstorben","1225–1299":"1225–1299","1260–1300":"1260–1300","1227–Female":"1227–Verstorben","1227":"1227","1225":"1225","1300":"1300","1299":"1299","1260":"1260","Dunbar Castle, East Lothian, Scotland":"Du